<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<quiz>
    <question>
        <prompt>The Smoot-Hawley Tariff's effect on international trade was:</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Increased global commerce</option>
            <option letter="b">Triggered retaliatory tariffs and reduced trade</option>
            <option letter="c">Improved diplomatic relations</option>
            <option letter="d">Strengthened American exports</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>The Smoot-Hawley Tariff of 1930 triggered retaliatory tariffs from other nations and severely reduced international trade. By raising U.S. tariffs to record-high levels on over 20,000 imported goods, it prompted other countries to impose their own high tariffs. This cycle of protectionism contributed to the deepening and spreading of the Great Depression globally.</explanation>
    </question>
</quiz>
